commit.message: CI: Update node-script versions due to deprecation warnings

Update CI to test gem install and gem use with source and binary gems

- Bump ruby versions
- Print logs in case of errors while building binary gems
- Don't use bundler cache for gem testing, because this would enable $pwd/vendor and wouldn't use the installed libusb gem.
- Remove platforms not (yet) supported by binary gems
- Download libusb tar before "rake gem"
- Use a dedicated Gemfile to avoid in-tree lib, but use installed libusb.gem
- Run cmpile task only explicit, so that CI runs with binary gems don't compile.
restrict yard version to avoid insecure versions
Add a missing build directory to "rake clean"
Add tests for Context#wrap_sys_device

Add LIBUSB::Device.max_alt_packet_size

Introduced in libusb-1.0.27 as libusb_get_max_alt_packet_size()

Add tests for new functions of libusb-1.0.27-rc1

Also add patches to fix libusb_set_option behavior reg. log callback
Add global set_option and set_options

Add support for new functions of libusb-1.0.27

They are:
- libusb_init_context
- libusb_set_log_cb
- libusb_wrap_sys_device

commit.message:
Cancel USB transfers on any exceptions

.. not only LIBUSB::Error, but also Interrupt or IRB::Abort, etc.

Otherwise incomplete transfers lead to LIBUSB::ERROR_BUSY at the next command.
